-- New Zealand Extends Chinese Visitor Visa Period to Two Years
-- B y   T r a c y   W i t h e r s
-- 2013-04-09T19:49:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-09/new-zealand-extends-chinese-visitor-visa-period-to-two-years.html
New Zealand  will extend the
duration of multiple entry visitor visas for Chinese travelers
to two years from one year, Prime Minister John Key said in an
e-mailed statement.  The change, applying to independent travelers not on an
organized tour, is effective from May 1 and means a visitor can
return within two years without repeating the visa application
proocess, he said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Tracy Withers at 
 twithers@bloomberg.net  